oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Pre-Columbian Panamanian cermaic vessel with applique decoration
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pre-Columbian vessel with an oval shape and a mouth offset from the center. A raised band with incised lines wraps around the vessel shoulder, curling up towards the rim on one side. Two protruding nodules extend from the shoulder on this side.
Rim is chipped in one area.
